This paper discusses index structures, which are commonly used in database systems to improve performance. Therefore, cs.DB (Database) is the most likely category. The paper also proposes a novel approximate index structure, which falls under the category of data structures (cs.DS). The paper discusses a cost model to help choose appropriate parameters, which is related to information retrieval (cs.IR) and artificial intelligence (cs.AI). Finally, the paper discusses the impact of index structures on system resources, which is related to software engineering (cs.SE).
